							<h3 class="invis">Author bio</h3>
																																															<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/andrew-engelson/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_bottom" >
											<div class="container col3 ">
												<div class="col span2"><p>Andrew Engelson is an award-winning freelance journalist and editor with a passion for narrative journalism. In a career spanning more than 20 years, he’s covered a wide range of topics, from the environment and climate science to social justice and LGBTQ issues. His work has appeared at <em>Investigate West</em>, <em>Crosscut</em>, <em>Columbia Insight</em>, <em>PubliCola</em>, <em>The Urbanist</em>, <em>High Country News</em>, <em>The Stranger</em>, and many other publications. He lives in Seattle, Washington, and can often be found hiking or skate skiing in the Cascade and Olympic Mountains.</p></div>
												<div class="singlebioimage col nomobile"><img width="520" height="520" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/andrew-engelson-520x520.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="writer Andrew Engelson" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/andrew-engelson-520x520.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/andrew-engelson-150x150.jpg 150w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/andrew-engelson-768x768.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/andrew-engelson-900x900.jpg 900w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/andrew-engelson.jpg 1000w" sizes="(max-width: 520px) 100vw, 520px" /></div>
